<HEADLINE>
FT  09 JUN 93 / Bolivia deficit highest for decade
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTINA LAMB
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   LA PAZ
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Bolivia's trade deficit was far greater last year than feared, rising to its
highest level in more than a decade and damping hopes of growth, according
to central bank figures, Christina Lamb writes from La Paz. The deficit
reached Dollars 561m in 1992, way above the original estimate of Dollars
410m. Imports reached a record Dollars 1.169bn while exports fell from
Dollars 760m to Dollars 608m. This was mainly because of a 50 per cent drop
in the value of hydrocarbon exports due to the ending of a fixed price
agreement on gas sales to Argentina.
