<TEXT>
THE POLITICAL row over the Rosyth and Devonport dockyards threatened to
erupt again last night as it emerged that Mr John Major will today meet Tory
MPs from south-west England who want Devonport to refit Britain's nuclear
submarine fleet, Ralph Atkins writes.
Mr Gordon Brown, Labour's trade and industry spokesman, demanded that he
should also be able to see the prime minister to put the case for Rosyth, in
