Major and said Rosyth would prove cheaper. However, south-west Tories are
confident the arguement is going their way.
MPs believe an announcement - which could cause more divisions in
Conservative ranks - is imminent, although Whitehall officials played down
suggestions that cabinet would reach a decision as early as this Thursday.
The government has said both Royal dockyards will be kept open.
