25 per cent. However this block is potentially for sale.
The next biggest holder is the Caisse de Depot, Quebec's CDollars 42bn
public pension fund, with 13.5 per cent. The Caisse has already indicated it
wants to keep effective control of Univa in Quebec.
Earlier this year the Caisse opposed a CDollars 11 a share bid from New York
investment bankers Blackstone Group for all Univa shares totalling about
CDollars 1bn.
