FT  08 JUN 93 / International Company News: Lower tax and interest prop
Email
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BRUCE JACQUES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
EMAIL, the Australian domestic appliance maker, reports net profits little
changed for the year ended March, thanks to a steep decline in interest
costs and a lower tax bill.
On sales 6 per cent higher at ADollars 1.47bn (USDollars 1bn), the company
made profits after abnormal items of ADollars 55.5m, against ADollars 55.3m
a year earlier. The dividend is going up from 17 to 17.5 cents a share.
Email's interest costs fell from ADollars 15.7m to ADollars 6.5m as a result
of reduced borrowings and lower interest rates. The year's result takes in a
strong second half, during which net earnings rose 13.5 per cent after a
weak start.
Email predicts a profit improvement in the current year with betting
trading. It said exports had continued to grow and margins were increasing
despite strong competitive pressure.
