<HEADLINE>
FT  08 JUN 93 / UK Company News: Western Selection
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
At March 31 1993 net asset value of Western Selection, the investment
finance company, was 18.82p, and 21.75p taking the market value of listed
associated undertakings.
Operating profit for the half year to March fell from Pounds 27,000 to
Pounds 24,000, but the previous period had to combat costs of Pounds 50,000
from discontinued operations. Earnings per share were 0.16p (losses 0.11p).
The half year included the dividend from Burlington Group. It was maintained
but the gross amount fell because of the reduced credits available following
the Budget.
Western has a 39.6 per cent holding in Creston. The latter plans an
acquisition for shares, which Western supports, and that will reduce its
stake to 15.3 per cent.
