<HEADLINE>
FT  08 JUN 93 / UK Company News: Lofs
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
AS A result of losses in its new vessel, London &amp; Overseas Freighters saw
pre-tax profit fall from Dollars 2.67m to Dollars 1.86m (Pounds 1.2m) in the
year to March 31.
The accounts are now stated in dollars as the company moved its domicile to
Bermuda a year ago. The dividend this time is 2 cents gross, which will be
converted into sterling unless individual shareholders decide otherwise. The
1991-92 payment was 1.25p net.
Directors said the reduced profit could be blamed on trading of the acquired
Nestor, now renamed London Enterprise. Its losses have been Dollars 630,000
since being transferred from Scoresby.
This year London Enterprise will be overhauled with consequent loss of
revenue. In mid-July the newly built tanker London Pride should be delivered
to trade under the profitable charter to Chevron.
