<HEADLINE>
FT  08 JUN 93 / UK Company News: Aberdeen Trust
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Aberdeen Trust, the investment and unit trust management company, reported
profits of Pounds 981,000 pre-tax for the six months to March 31.
The outcome, achieved on turnover of Pounds 7.15m (Pounds 5.59m), compared
with profits last time of Pounds 1.04m and was struck after reorganisation
costs totalling Pounds 600,000, including a compensation payment of Pounds
150,000 to a former director for loss of office.
The costs masked a sharp improvement at the operating level - profits moved
ahead from Pounds 1.19m to Pounds 2.07m - reflecting strong growth in fund
management and currency benefits. Interest charges, however, jumped from
Pounds 221,000 to Pounds 523,000 as a result of the transaction last
September with Century Life.
Earnings per share dipped to 0.81p (0.97p) and the interim dividend is
halved to 0.5p; a final of 1p is forecast, however, which would maintain the
total at 1.5p.
</TEXT>
