FT  08 JUN 93 / UK Company News: Further distribution likely at Manakin
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Manakin Holdings, the investment trust which went into voluntary liquidation
in 1991, reported a net asset value of 68p at April 15, against 100p six
months earlier. During the period two distributions totalling 42p were made.
It is expected that a further repayment will be made before the end of 1993.
There was a net loss for the six months to April 15 of Pounds 188,000,
against profits of Pounds 257,000. Losses per share were 0.96p (earnings
1.25p).
