FT  08 JUN 93 / Letter: Not so good with VAT numbers
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Dr GORDON WILKINSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Charles Batchelor ('Negotiating the barriers', June 1) rightly refers
to the difficulties and burdensome administration of new rules on
value-added tax, especially the completion of statistical trading reports.
One might be impressed by the apparent sophistication of Customs &amp; Excise
computer systems to process such volumes of trade data.
However, we find it astonishing that VAT offices are able to confirm whether
a VAT number applies to a particular European company, but, given the names,
are unable to advise the correct VAT number for the occasional firms that
our time-consuming and expensive mail, fax and phone communications have
been unsuccessful in obtaining.
Gordon Wilkinson,
Infocom,
