FT  07 JUN 93 / Construction Contracts: Pounds 10m orders awarded to Hall &amp;
Tawse
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
HALL &amp; TAWSE, the construction division of Raine, has won contracts in the
education sector worth over Pounds 10m.
A three and a half storey business school is to be built at a cost of Pounds
3.2m for the University of Derby, including two new lecture theatres with
seating for 400 students.
One of the theatres will feature a mock courtroom to help students on law
degree courses familiarise themselves with judiciary surroundings. (This
contract follows the construction of a new Pounds 3m science and technology
building at the university last September.)
Hall &amp; Tawse has also commenced work on a Pounds 2.2m contract to build a
music wing at the University of Nottingham's Art Centre.
The 57-week building programme will see the development of a recital hall,
14 practice rooms, a music library, and a separate seminar room.
In Worcestershire, a Pounds 1.8m order has been won to design and build a
library and resource centre at Bromsgrove School.
It will have a capacity for 30,000 books, and provide 100 study spaces.
